      "rationale": "Inlet flow rates and rotational speeds for the five CPB operating points were prescribed from the FDA benchmark test protocol. Blood analogue fluid (glycerol-water, dynamic viscosity 3.5 mPa·s at 37°C) properties matched to within 2% of laboratory-measured values. Inlet turbulence intensity set to 5% based on upstream tubing characterisation. All boundary condition values and their uncertainties documented in test report TR-CPB-2024-07."
