      "rationale": "NIH is the standard FDA-recognised metric for pump-induced hemolysis and directly correlates with plasma free haemoglobin (pfHb) elevation measured in in-vitro loop tests. The relative hemolysis index RH (ratio of device NIH to predicate NIH) is the acceptance criterion (RH < 1), consistent with FDA guidance on 510(k) submissions for CPB devices. QoI relevance is confirmed."
    },
