      "rationale": "Validation activities used the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry, the same impeller diameter and volute design as the device under assessment. Fluid properties and rotational speed ranges overlap substantially with the CPB operating envelope. The Morrison et al. (2019) dataset provides hemolysis measurements for a centrifugal pump family, and the assessment team judged the geometric and fluid-dynamic similarity sufficient for MRL 2. The team noted that the operating duration per experimental run (4 hours continuous) is representative of CPB procedure lengths."
