    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required Gradation levels for MRL 2. The six non-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out per ASME V&V 40 Table 3 for this model risk level. Validation evidence from the Morrison et al. (2019) experimental dataset demonstrates NIH prediction within ±18% across the CPB operating envelope with no systematic bias. Grid convergence is confirmed (GCI_fine = 3.1%). The assessment team concludes that the CFD model has sufficient credibility to support identification of worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device, and that the relative hemolysis index RH < 1 acceptance criterion can be evaluated with confidence at MRL 2. Decision: Accepted.",
